# Liabilities Exposures Debt Securities Issued In Period Amount

## identifier
de15111

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of debt securities issued during the relevant period. These are transferable instruments evidencing a relationship of indebtedness. They are characterised by having a definable return that is not based on the economic performance of the issuing entity. Securities are classified as debt or equity in accordance with the relevant accounting standards.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=credit
- name=Liabilities.Exposures.DebtSecuritiesIssuedInPeriod.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo3.02.19
- period=duration
